# Impute missing values in 'children' with 0

# Fill missing 'country' values with 'Unknown'
df['country'].fillna('Unknown', inplace=True)

# Fill missing 'agent' values with 'No Agent' (use 0 or another placeholder)
df['agent'].fillna(0, inplace=True)

# Fill missing 'company' values with 'No Company'
df['company'].fillna(0, inplace=True)

# Ensure 'reservation_status_date' is in datetime format
df['reservation_status_date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['reservation_status_date'])

# Extract the month from 'reservation_status_date'
df['month'] = df['reservation_status_date'].dt.month

# Plotting the count plot
plt.figure(figsize=(16, 8))
ax1 = sns.countplot(x='month', hue='is_canceled', data=df, palette='bright')
legend_labels, _ = ax1.get_legend_handles_labels()
ax1.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))
plt.title('Reservation status per month', size=20)
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Number of reservations')
plt.legend(['Not canceled', 'Canceled'])
plt.show()

In [74]:
# Calculate average daily rate for canceled reservations
cancelled_df_adr = cancelled_date.groupby('reservation_status_date')[['adr']].mean()
cancelled_df_adr.reset_index(inplace=True)
cancelled_df_adr.sort_values('reservation_status_date', inplace=True)

# Calculate average daily rate for non-canceled reservations
not_cancelled_data = df[df['is_canceled'] == 0]
not_cancelled_df_adr = not_cancelled_data.groupby('reservation_status_date')[['adr']].mean()
not_cancelled_df_adr.reset_index(inplace=True)
not_cancelled_df_adr.sort_values('reservation_status_date', inplace=True)

# Plotting
plt.figure(figsize=(20, 6))
plt.title('Average Daily Rate')
plt.plot(not_cancelled_df_adr['reservation_status_date'], not_cancelled_df_adr['adr'], label='Not Canceled')
plt.plot(cancelled_df_adr['reservation_status_date'], cancelled_df_adr['adr'], label='Canceled')
plt.legend(fontsize = 15)
plt.show()
